---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import AffiliateLink from '../components/AffiliateLink.astro';

const meta = {
  title: 'v0.dev vs Cursor: AI Code Tools Compared (2025)',
  description: 'Honest comparison: v0.dev is free AI code generator for React. Cursor is AI-powered code editor. Which should you use? Different tools for different needs.',
  image: '/og-image.svg',
  keywords: ['v0.dev vs Cursor', 'AI code generator', 'Cursor AI', 'v0.dev review', 'AI coding tools'],
};
---

<Layout {...meta}>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-[#FEF9F3] py-12 sm:py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <p class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-black text-[#E07A5F] mb-4 tracking-[0.3em] uppercase">
        Tested · Honest · No Hype
      </p>

      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-black mb-6 leading-tight">
        v0.dev vs Cursor: Apples and Oranges
      </h1>

      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 mb-8">
        People compare these like they're competitors. They're not. v0.dev generates code from prompts. Cursor is an AI-powered editor where you write code with AI assistance. Completely different tools for different needs.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-[#E07A5F]/10 border-2 border-[#E07A5F] rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
          Quick answer: Use <AffiliateLink href="https://v0.dev">v0.dev</AffiliateLink> to generate React components from scratch. Use <AffiliateLink href="https://cursor.com">Cursor</AffiliateLink> as your daily code editor with AI assistance. They work together, not against each other.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          v0.dev: Free, generates code, great for starting from zero. Cursor: $20/mo, AI-assisted editing, great for ongoing development. Most serious developers use both.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What They Actually Are -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      What These Tools Actually Do
    </h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <!-- v0.dev -->
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4"><AffiliateLink href="https://v0.dev">v0.dev</AffiliateLink></h3>
        <p class="font-bold mb-2">AI Code Generator</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">You describe what you want in plain English. v0 generates React/Next.js code. You can iterate, refine, and download the actual code.</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Prompt → Code:</strong> Describe UI, get implementation</li>
          <li>• <strong>Iterate:</strong> Refine with follow-up prompts</li>
          <li>• <strong>Export:</strong> Download actual React code</li>
          <li>• <strong>Free:</strong> Generous free tier</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Cursor -->
      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4"><AffiliateLink href="https://cursor.com">Cursor</AffiliateLink></h3>
        <p class="font-bold mb-2">AI-Powered Code Editor</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">It's VS Code with AI built in. Write code, get AI suggestions, chat with your codebase, generate from natural language. Full development environment.</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Code editor:</strong> Full IDE like VS Code</li>
          <li>• <strong>AI autocomplete:</strong> Suggests code as you type</li>
          <li>• <strong>Chat with code:</strong> Ask questions about your project</li>
          <li>• <strong>$20/mo:</strong> Paid tool with free tier</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Key Differences -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Key Differences
    </h2>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-gray-100">
            <th class="p-4 border font-bold">Feature</th>
            <th class="p-4 border font-bold"><AffiliateLink href="https://v0.dev">v0.dev</AffiliateLink></th>
            <th class="p-4 border font-bold"><AffiliateLink href="https://cursor.com">Cursor</AffiliateLink></th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td class="p-4 border">Primary use</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Generate from scratch</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Edit and iterate</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 border">Interface</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Web chat</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Full IDE</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="p-4 border">Output</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">React components</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Full projects</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 border">Pricing</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Free</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">$20/mo (Pro)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="p-4 border">Best for</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Starting from zero</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Ongoing development</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 border">Learning curve</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Zero (just prompt)</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">Low (if you know VS Code)</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- When to Use v0.dev -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Use v0.dev When:
    </h2>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
      <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
        <li>• <strong>You're starting from zero:</strong> Blank page, need a component</li>
        <li>• <strong>You know what you want:</strong> Can describe the UI clearly</li>
        <li>• <strong>You want fast iteration:</strong> Generate, review, refine with prompts</li>
        <li>• <strong>You're building UI:</strong> React components, landing pages, dashboards</li>
        <li>• <strong>You want full ownership:</strong> Export clean code, self-host</li>
        <li>• <strong>You're budget-conscious:</strong> Free tier is generous</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 mt-6">
        <p class="font-black mb-3">Example workflow:</p>
        <ol class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>1. Prompt: "Create a pricing table with 3 tiers"</li>
          <li>2. v0 generates React component</li>
          <li>3. Prompt: "Make the middle tier stand out with a gradient"</li>
          <li>4. v0 refines the component</li>
          <li>5. Download code, paste into your project</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- When to Use Cursor -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Use Cursor When:
    </h2>

    <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
      <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
        <li>• <strong>You're building a full project:</strong> Not just components</li>
        <li>• <strong>You need context awareness:</strong> AI understands your entire codebase</li>
        <li>• <strong>You're editing existing code:</strong> Refactoring, debugging, extending</li>
        <li>• <strong>You want AI autocomplete:</strong> Suggestions as you type</li>
        <li>• <strong>You're working in a team:</strong> Full IDE features, git integration</li>
        <li>• <strong>Price isn't a barrier:</strong> $20/mo is worth it for serious development</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 mt-6">
        <p class="font-black mb-3">Example workflow:</p>
        <ol class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>1. Open your project in Cursor (like VS Code)</li>
          <li>2. Start typing a function, AI suggests completion</li>
          <li>3. Highlight code, press Cmd+K to edit with AI</li>
          <li>4. Ask Cursor: "Why is this test failing?" It analyzes and explains</li>
          <li>5. Continue development in the same editor</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How They Work Together -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      How They Work Together
    </h2>

    <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
      <p class="font-black mb-4">Best workflow: Use both. They complement each other.</p>

      <ol class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
        <li><strong>Step 1:</strong> Use <AffiliateLink href="https://v0.dev">v0.dev</AffiliateLink> to generate initial components. Pricing tables, hero sections, contact forms.</li>

        <li><strong>Step 2:</strong> Export the code and add to your project in Cursor.</li>

        <li><strong>Step 3:</strong> Use Cursor to customize the components. Add your business logic, connect to APIs, handle edge cases.</li>

        <li><strong>Step 4:</strong> Use Cursor's AI for ongoing development. Debugging, refactoring, extending features.</li>

        <li><strong>Step 5:</strong> When you need new UI components, go back to v0.dev.</li>
      </ol>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mt-6">You get v0.dev's generation speed + Cursor's development power. Best of both worlds.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing Comparison -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Pricing Reality
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-black mb-2"><AffiliateLink href="https://v0.dev">v0.dev</AffiliateLink>: $0</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Completely free for individual developers. Generate unlimited components. Export unlimited code. Only pay if you want premium features or team collaboration (rarely needed).</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-black mb-2"><AffiliateLink href="https://cursor.com">Cursor</AffiliateLink>: $20/month (Pro)</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Free tier available with limits. Pro is $20/mo for unlimited AI usage. Business is $40/mo. If you code daily, $20/mo is trivial. Pays for itself in saved time within a week.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-black mb-2">The math:</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">v0.dev for generation (free). Cursor for development ($240/year). Total: $240/year for a powerful AI-assisted workflow. Compare to your hourly rate. If this saves you 3 hours per year, it's profitable. It saves 3 hours per week minimum.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Which Should You Choose? -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Which Should You Choose?
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✅ Start with v0.dev if:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• You're new to coding</li>
          <li>• You just need a few components</li>
          <li>• Budget is $0</li>
          <li>• You want to test an idea quickly</li>
          <li>• You're building a marketing site or landing pages</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✅ Add Cursor if:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• You're building a real application</li>
          <li>• You need ongoing AI assistance</li>
          <li>• You're working in an existing codebase</li>
          <li>• You want context-aware AI that knows your project</li>
          <li>• $20/mo fits your budget</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-black mb-3">Most developers end up with both:</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Start with v0.dev because it's free. When you hit its limits (need full IDE, context awareness, ongoing development), try Cursor. If Cursor saves you time, keep it. If not, you're out nothing.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Bottom Line -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <div class="bg-[#E07A5F]/10 border-2 border-[#E07A5F] rounded-xl p-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-black mb-6">The Bottom Line</h2>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">These aren't competitors. They're different tools:</p>

      <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700 mb-6">
        <li>• <strong>v0.dev:</strong> AI code generator. Prompt → React component. Free. Best for starting from zero.</li>
        <li>• <strong>Cursor:</strong> AI-powered code editor. Full IDE with AI assistance. $20/mo. Best for ongoing development.</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">Don't choose one. Use both together.</p>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700">Generate components in v0.dev (free). Develop your project in Cursor ($20/mo). Get the best of generation and editing. This is how most serious developers work in 2025.</p>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mt-6">If you can only pick one: v0.dev for beginners and one-off projects. Cursor for serious developers building real applications.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black mb-6 text-gray-900">
      Related Tool Guides
    </h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <a href="/v0-dev-review" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">v0.dev Full Review</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Deep dive on v0.dev</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/durable-vs-v0-vs-framer" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Durable vs v0 vs Framer</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">AI website builders compared</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
